member.summary: Ignore VLAN tags on received frames. VLAN tags are not added nor removed from the frames. If a frame has a VLAN tag, then it is retained. If a frame does not have a VLAN tag, then no tag is added.

member.name: F:Skyline.DataMiner.Library.NetInsightNimbra.VlanMode.Customer
member.summary: VLAN-handling in accordance with IEEE 802.1Q. Frames are forwarded and filtered according to customer VLAN tag. Frames that are not tagged are tagged with default VLAN tag as configured on the interface.

member.name: F:Skyline.DataMiner.Library.NetInsightNimbra.VlanMode.Provider
member.summary: VLAN-handling in accordance with IEEE 802.1ad. Frames are forwarded and filtered according to service VLAN tag.Any customer VLAN is ignored. Frames that are not tagged are tagged with default VLAN tag as configured on the interface.

IF previous node has resource assigned script should identify the DCF output interface related to the resource assigned to that previous node based on DCF , it should look at all other resources connected to it and limit the drop down of current node with intersect between those connected resources and all candidate resource( using regular filtering mechanism already available in the solution) ELSE(previous node does not have resource assigned) dropdown remains empty ELSE(no DCF property) regular workflow.

member.summary: A Reservation is not attached to a Booking Manager but it is created by one. In the presence of Multiple Booking Managers the user MUST use the Virtual Platform parameter present in the Booking Manager equal to the Element Parameter. This method will look for all Elements that are create with protocols whose name start by "Skyline Booking Manager" then it. Then it looks for the Virtual Platform parameters for each element and tries to match them. If one match occurs, the Element is returned. If no match occurs, the first element is returned. If no elements are found using a protocol with name starting with "Skyline Booking Manager" an exception is thrown.
member.returns: Returns a Booking Manager Element. It might be that the returned value is not the element that hosts the reservation.
member.exception: If no Skyline Booking Manager Element is found.

If the combination of the Service Definition Name and the Parent System Function name exceeds 98 chars the algorithm will truncate the strings privileging the Parent System Function Name to use as much chars as possible. 98 Chars value is related with DataMiner is only capable of assigning a maximum of 111 chars long visio filename. Note: DataMiner doesn't support longer names for Visios, which means the protocol name must be limited upfront.
